==English==

===Proverb===
'''[[don't]] [[look]] a [[gift horse]] in the [[mouth]]'''

# A phrase referring to [[unappreciatively]] [[questioning]] of a [[gift]] or [[handout]] too closely. Horses gum's recede as they age making the teeth appear to grow long. Therefore, inspecting the teeth of a horse given as a gift would mean that recipient is trying to see if the horse is old or young. 

